        "text": "The Basel Reading Society was one of countless societies that emerged in 18th century Europe. It was initially open exclusively to men from Basel's middle classes, and it was mainly wealthy people who could afford to join. Today, however, our members include a broad spectrum of men and women from Switzerland and abroad, whose numbers have risen to well over a thousand. The reading rooms are open to members and subscribers every day of the year, and the stock of our lending library is constantly being expanded."
